    <text>
        <front>
            <div type="editorial_desc">
                <p>Presidential candidates Abraham Lincoln and George McClellan are shown in the
                    middle of a horse race. At the left of the cartoon, Lincoln is in the lead as he
                    rides "The Union Roadster," a horse labeled "Slow and Steady." He holds an
                    American flag, labeled "Union, The Government, Laws," topped by a liberty cap.
                    In the middle, McClellan is shown trying to ride two horses at once (a common
                    circus trick at the time); he has one foot on the back of "Mac's War-Horse,"
                    labeled "Brag &amp; Bluster," and his other foot on the back of "The Peace
                    Donkey," labeled "Fawn &amp; Cringe." This likely refers to McClellan's attempts
                    to campaign both on his military reputation as a Union general and on a platform
                    of reconciliation with the South. The donkey carries a sack labeled "Rebel War
                    Debt," filled with notes, and kicks behind him. Behind the donkey is a
                    McClellan's running mate, George H. Pendleton of Ohio, dressed as a circus clown
                    or jester. Pendleton whips the donkey and holds a scroll that reads "Peace!
                    Peace! Anything for Peace!" At far right, in the background, a man standing in a
                    carriage, watching the race through a pair of binoculars, predicts Lincoln's
                    victory in a thick accent. The Library of Congress and other historians identify
                    this man as a stereotype of a Jewish peddler.</p>
            </div>
        </front>

        <body>
            <div type="image_transcription" n="1" facs="#title">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial">Title</supplied></head>
                <p>SLOW &amp; STEADY WINS THE RACE.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="image_transcription" n="2" facs="#lincoln_horse">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial">The Union Roadster (<persName key="ENT.000000447"
                            >Lincoln</persName>'s horse)</supplied></head>
                <p>THE <sic>UION</sic> ROADSTER.</p>
                <p>SLOW AND STEADY.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="image_transcription" n="3" facs="#lincoln">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial"><persName key="ENT.000000447">Abraham
                            Lincoln</persName></supplied></head>
                <p>This reminds me of a story I once heard out West.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="image_transcription" n="4" facs="#flag">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial"><rs ref="cartoons_symbols.xml#liberty_cap">Liberty
                            cap</rs> and American flag</supplied></head>
                <p>LIBERTY</p>
                <p>UNION THE GOVERN<supplied resp="editorial">MENT</supplied>, LAWS</p>
            </div>
            <div type="image_transcription" n="5" facs="#mac_horse">
                <head><persName key="ENT.000001783">MAC</persName>'S WAR-HORSE</head>
                <p>BRAG &amp; BLUSTER</p>
            </div>
            <div type="image_transcription" n="6" facs="#donkey">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial"><rs ref="cartoons_symbols.xml#donkey">Donkey</rs>
                        (carrying sack)</supplied></head>
                <p>The Peace Donkey.</p>
                <p>FAWN &amp; CRINGE.</p>
                <p>REBEL WAR DEBT</p>
                <p><unclear reason="handwriting"/> FOR <persName key="ENT.000001783"
                    >MAC</persName></p>
                <p>SERVICE OF <unclear reason="handwriting"/></p>
                <p><persName key="ENT.000002824">LEE</persName>'S SAL<unclear reason="handwriting"
                    /></p>
                <p>ARIES of <choice>
                        <sic>CONFDERA</sic>
                        <corr>CONFEDERATE</corr>
                    </choice> OFFICIALS</p>
            </div>
            <div type="image_transcription" n="7" facs="#mac">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial"><persName key="ENT.000001783">George
                            McClellan</persName></supplied></head>
                <p>I've seen many a Clown ride two horses that never saw West-Point</p>
            </div>
            <div type="image_transcription" n="8" facs="#clown">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial"><persName key="ENT.000003373">George
                            Pendleton</persName></supplied></head>
                <p>The Ohio Clown.</p>
                <p>Go on, you ugly beast!</p>
                <p>PEACE! PEACE! Anything for PEACE</p>
            </div>
            <div type="image_transcription" n="9" facs="#peddler">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial">Jewish peddler</supplied></head>
                <p>By mine <choice>
                        <orig>Faders</orig>
                        <corr>Fathers</corr>
                    </choice>, Abraham, Isaac, and <sic>Jacobs</sic>, I <choice>
                        <orig>peleif</orig>
                        <corr>believe</corr>
                    </choice> de <persName key="ENT.000000447">Old Abe</persName> will win!</p>
            </div>
            <div type="image_transcription" n="10" facs="#note">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial">Note</supplied></head>
                <p><add><unclear reason="handwriting">HeG 10 1877 of be</unclear></add></p>
            </div>
        </body>

